    "title": "DOMAIN_SEPARATOR does not adjust to the changes in block.chainid or address(this)",
    "content": "## Security Report\n\n## Severity\n**Low Risk**\n\n## Context\n(No context files were provided by the reviewer)\n\n## Description\nIn the file `AToken.sol` from lines 134 to 142, it has been identified that if a fork occurs, the `DOMAIN_SEPARATOR` does not get recalculated automatically. Instead, the proxy needs to be reinitialized.\n\n## Recommendation\nIf `block.chainid` or `address(this)` changes, ensure to recalculate the `DOMAIN_SEPARATOR`.\n\n## Astera\nFixed in commit `f3ca85f8`.\n\n## Spearbit\nThe fix only considers the change in `block.chainid` to recalculate the domain separator and does not take into account `address(this)`.",
